02/01/2009
PRISTINA, Kosovo -- A total of 55 people suffered fireworks-caused injuries on New Year's Eve in Kosovo, police said on Thursday (January 1st). 
Despite the incidents, security across the country was under control during celebrations, authorities said. 
This was Kosovo's first New Year's celebration as an independent state. 
(Alsat, Telegrafi, KTV - 01/01/09)
